  "prompt": "Who made our constitution?",
  "response": "The United States Constitution was primarily drafted by the Founding Fathers during the Constitutional Convention in Philadelphia, Pennsylvania, from May 25 to September 17, 1787. Key figures involved in its creation included:\n\n1. James Madison (often called the \"Father of the Constitution\")\n2. George Washington (President of the Convention)\n3. Alexander Hamilton\n4. Benjamin Franklin\n5. Gouverneur Morris\n6. Roger Sherman\n7. Charles Pinckney\n8. James Wilson\n\nThe document was the result of extensive debates and compromises among delegates from 12 of the 13 original states (Rhode Island did not send representatives). After the drafting, the Constitution was ratified by the states and went into effect in 1789. The first ten amendments, known as the Bill of Rights, were added in 1791 to address concerns about individual liberties.",
